snippet: The vast majority of candidates in Tuesday’s open, nonpartisan primary who advanced to the fall election were registered Republicans and Democrats.
abstract: News analysis; vast majority of candidates who advanced after California's first nonpartisan primary are registered Republicans and Democrats, upending expectations that the new method would provide a wave of independent candidates.
lead_paragraph: The vast majority of candidates in Tuesday’s open, nonpartisan primary who advanced to the fall election were registered Republicans and Democrats.

headline.main: California’s Nonpartisan Primary Shows Independents to Be in Short Supply
headline.print_headline: California’s Nonpartisan Primary Shows Independents to Be in Short Supply
